# One package per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
# Edit this file for your chroot, then run chroot-minimize.sh (dry-run by default).
#
# Intention: drop desktop / print / mail stacks that are rarely useful in a phone chroot
# and often fail postinst under NetHunter. Comment anything you still want.
#
# --- Display / desktop (if pulled in) ---
# lightdm
# xserver-xorg
#
# --- Mail (common postinst pain in chroot) ---
# Do NOT auto-remove exim4 here: apt often replaces with courier-mta and yanks Xfce/kali metas (verify dry-run first).
# exim4-daemon-light
# exim4-base
# exim4-config
# postfix
#
# --- Printing (no printer on device) ---
cups
cups-daemon
cups-browsed
cups-client
cups-core-drivers
cups-filters
cups-ipp-utils
cups-ppdc
cups-server-common
#
# --- Bluetooth UI (headless) ---
# blueman
# bluez-cups
#
# --- Large desktop apps (uncomment if present) ---
# libreoffice-core
# thunderbird
# wireshark-qt
#
# --- Orphaned metas: add only what `aptitude why` / manual review says is safe ---
